    <h1 class="opener__hed  opener__hed--light" >        Arizona Regulators Closed a Failing Charter School. It Reopened as a Private Religious School Funded by Taxpayers.
    </h1>

    
            <div class="article-meta-1  article-meta-1--light">
            <span class="article-meta-1__byline">
                by <a class="name" href="https://www.propublica.org/people/eli-hager">Eli Hager</a>            </span>
            <time class="article-meta-1__pubdate">
                <time class="timestamp" datetime="2024-12-31EST06:00">Dec. 31, 6 a.m. EST</time>
            </time>
        </div>
    
    </div> <!-- Close .opener__topic-title-dek-wrapper -->

            <div class="content"> <!-- not sure if this is the best way to reestablish the text column -->
            <h2 class="opener__dek opener__dek--match-text-column" style="display: none">                Arizona’s acclaimed voucher program provides zero transparency into private schools’ history, academic performance or financial sustainability to help parents make informed school choices.
            </h2>
        </div>
    
</div>
        
