                    srcset="https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20241224-oil-arkle-opener.png?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=105&amp;q=80&amp;w=105&amp;s=fe6399d064d2c5c5269998f1173e5d10 105w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20241224-oil-arkle-opener.png?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=210&amp;q=80&amp;w=210&amp;s=418b9478f9a9f77975ee2fff065e493e 210w"
                    width="105"
                    height="105"
                    loading="lazy"
                    js-autosizes
                />
            </a>
        </div>
    
    <div class="story-card__description">
                        <a class="story-card__series" href="https://www.propublica.org/series/unplugged">Unplugged</a>
        
        <h3 class="story-card__hed" >
            <a href="https://www.propublica.org/article/oil-orphan-wells-cleanup-playbook-siana-tom-ragsdale">
                                    The American Oil Industry’s Playbook, Illustrated: How Drillers Offload Costly Cleanup Onto the Public
                            </a>
        </h3>

        <p class="story-card__dek" >
                            Oil executive Tom Ragsdale walked away from his old wells, making the pollution left behind the state of New Mexico’s problem. His tactics, however, are ubiquitous in the industry.
                    </p>

        <p class="story-card__byline">
            by <a class="name" href="https://www.propublica.org/people/mark-olalde">Mark Olalde</a>, illustrations by <a class="name" href="https://www.propublica.org/people/peter-arkle">Peter Arkle</a>,             <time class="timestamp" datetime="2024-12-30EST05:00">Dec. 30, 5 a.m. EST</time>
        </p>

            </div>
</div>
                            </div>
                    <div class="most-read-story">
                                    


        
                    
<div class="story-card story-card--standard">
    
    


                    
    
        <div class="lead-art thumbnail">
            <a class="aspect-1-1" href="https://www.propublica.org/article/thomas-weiner-montana-st-peters-hospital-oncology">
                <img
                    alt=""
                    src="data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D%27http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg%27%20width%3D%271%27%20height%3D%271%27%20style%3D%27background%3Atransparent%27%2F%3E"
                    srcset="https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/Montana-Doc-Promo.jpg?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=105&amp;q=75&amp;w=105&amp;s=ba8c9f5b6cd93a6f75ed7361b363b2c7 105w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/Montana-Doc-Promo.jpg?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=210&amp;q=75&amp;w=210&amp;s=9cb5149edcaa5de015e24c2e827a2254 210w"
